cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.DC, cs.SI 

This paper deals with network security and privacy, specifically in the context of Internet traffic routing and surveillance. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of overlay networks and DNS resolvers, which are relevant to the categories cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). The paper also involves analyzing and characterizing data, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
